Description: The Paulson Institute is a “think and do tank” that promotes sustainable growth and environmental protection in China and the United States.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: The Paulson Institute is an independent, non-partisan center headquartered in Chicago. Their Work is grounded in the principle that today’s most pressing economic and environmental challenges can be solved only if the United States and China work in complementary ways. With offices in the United States and China, and partners around the globe, they take a “think and do” approach. Their mission is to advance global environmental protection and sustainable economic growth in the United States and China, while fostering broader understanding between the two countries. The Institute was founded in 2011 by Henry M. Paulson, Jr., the 74th Secretary of the Treasury and former chief executive of Goldman Sachs to promote economic growth and environmental preservation in both countries through programs, advocacy and research. They work at the nexus of economic and environmental issues in the United States and China. Their programs in China focus on improving climate and air quality, advancing nature conservation and promoting sustainable cities. In the United States, they promote bilateral cross-border investment that will improve US-China relations and help create jobs. Their Think Tank publishes papers on the most important macroeconomic issues facing China today, energy strategies, and issues in US-China economic relations. They have offices in Chicago (at the University of Chicago), Washington and Beijing. Their work focuses on practical, cost-effective ways to save ecosystems, increase energy efficiency, reduce air pollution, develop more sustainable cities and improve US-China relations and the lives of the American and Chinese people—while supporting economic growth and reducing threats to the planet’s long-term survival.

Colored Regions: ZeeMaps provides capabilities to color various regions of     the world like cities, countries or states. Description: MeetingSense Software offers a hosted collaborative software solution for optimizing meeting productivity.
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: MeetingSense Software Corporation is a venture backed start up founded by former IBM and Macromedia management to address the emerging need among today's businesses for a simple but effective way to collaboratively manage meeting information and action items in order to optimize business productivity. In recent years, corporate globalization, expanding regulatory requirements, sophisticated new web conferencing technologies, and a surge in the risks and costs of travel have resulted in a dramatic increase in the cost and number meetings held by organizations, particularly web and telephone conferences that include diverse participants spread across wide geographic areas. As the quantity of meetings has risen, however, the quality has declined, and productivity has suffered. Meeting time is increasingly wasted due to a lack of structure, lost information, and mismanaged responsibilities. These problems are exacerbated when employees in different regions and from different fields of expertise collaborate over electronic media, with little or no personal rapport. The resulting inefficiencies impact all aspects of business and cost the global economy billions of dollars each year. In response to this pervasive problem, MeetingSense Software formed to provide a targeted, comprehensive solution. The goal was to develop software that would allow businesses to maximize their return on investment in meeting time and meeting technology by ensuring that each meeting, regardless of size, scope, or subject, is leveraged directly into productive action. The result is the company's flagship product, MeetingSense, a hosted collaborative software solution for optimizing meeting productivity.
